Admiral Bake was a famous gnome explorer from the Fourth Age.[1] He was best known for presenting the tortoise Mibbiwocket to King Healthorg the Great shortly after its birth.[2] This tortoise would go on to become the world's oldest tortoise.[2]

Admiral Bake is the correct answer to the Natural history quiz question: "Name the explorer who discovered the world's oldest tortoise."[3]

References[edit | edit source]

  1. ^ Hazelmere, "The Eyes of Glouphrie", Old School RuneScape. "I have a story to tell you that will answer most of your questions. Let us travel back in time, to the time you humans call the Fourth Age." Cutscene shows King Healthorg mounted on Mibbiwocket, who was a gift from Admiral Bake.
  2. ^ 2.0 2.1 Natural historian, "Varrock Museum", Old School RuneScape. "The oldest tortoise ever recorded was Mibbiwocket, who was presented to the King Healthorg the Great, by the famous explorer Admiral Bake, shortly after its birth."
  3. ^ Orlando Smith, "Natural history quiz", Old School RuneScape. "Name the explorer who discovered the world's oldest tortoise."
